{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"skipAsync","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"count","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and will result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"text":" errors.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A value of ","type":"text"},{"code":"count","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" larger than ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_MAXSSIZE"},{"text":" will cause a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"invalidArgument"},{"type":"text","text":" error."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes skipped will be passed to the callback.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is not an error if this is not the same as the requested size, as it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can happen e.g. near the end of a file, but generally we try to skip"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as many bytes as requested. Zero is returned on end of file","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(or if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"text":" is zero), but never otherwise.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any outstanding i\/o request with higher priority (lower numerical value)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be executed before an outstanding request with lower priority.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting classes."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"However, if you override one, you must override all."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/inputstreamprotocol\/skipasync(count:iopriority:cancellable:callback:userdata:)-9p0by"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStreamProtocol\/skipAsync(count:ioPriority:cancellable:callback:userData:)-9p0by"},"abstract":[{"text":"Request an asynchronous skip of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"count"},{"type":"text","text":" bytes f